sec.p:
So far, the analysis of DNA methylation in prenatal diagnosis pertains only the ImpDis and the triplet expansion disorders FXS and CDM1. Although prenatal diagnosis of FXS and CDM1 is based on the sizing of the triplet repeat, coupling it with DNA methylation analysis may ameliorate diagnostic accuracy. Molecular tests can be offered during the prenatal period, based on the presence of:
Abnormal fetal and/or parental karyotypes involving chromosomes harboring imprinted loci;
Positive family history;
Fetal phenotypes suggesting ImpDis detected by ultrasound;
Females carrying PM or FM of FXS and CDM1.
